{"title_page": "58th British Academy Film Awards", "text_new": "{{no footnotes|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number            = 58\n| award             = British Academy Film Awards\n| date              = 12 February 2005\n| site              = [[Odeon Leicester Square]], [[London]]\n| host              = [[Stephen Fry]]\n| producer          = \n| director          = \n| best_film         = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'''''\n| best_british      = '''''[[My Summer of Love]]'''''\n| best_actor        = '''[[Jamie Foxx]]'''\n| best_actor_film   = ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]''\n| best_actress      = '''[[Imelda Staunton]]'''\n| best_actress_film = ''[[Vera Drake]]''\n| most_wins         = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''''' (4)\n| most_nominations  = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''''' (14)\n| channel           = \n| duration          = \n| ratings           = \n| last              = 57th\n| next              = 59th\n}}\n\nThe '''58th [[British Academy Film Awards]]''', given by the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]], took place on 12 February 2005 and honoured the best films of [[2004 in film|2004]].\n\n''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' won [[BAFTA Award for Best Film|Best Film]], Best Supporting Actress for [[Cate Blanchett]], Best Production Design, and Best Makeup and Hair. [[Jamie Foxx]] and [[Imelda Staunton]] won Best Actor and Best Actress for ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' and ''[[Vera Drake]]'', respectively. ''Vera Drake'' also won Best Director for [[Mike Leigh]] and Best Costume Design. ''[[My Summer of Love]]'', directed by [[Pawe\u0142 Pawlikowski]], was voted Outstanding British Film of 2004.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n[[File:Mike Leigh (Berlinale 2012) cropped.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Mike Leigh]], Best Director winner]]\n[[File:Jamie Foxx by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Jamie Foxx]], Best Actor winner]]\n[[File:Imelda Staunton (2011).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Imelda Staunton]], Best Actress winner]]\n[[File:Clive Owen (Berlin Film Festival 2009).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Clive Owen]], Best Supporting Actor winner]]\n[[File:Cate Blanchett Cannes 2015.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Cate Blanchett]], Best Supporting Actress winner]]\n[[File:Charlie Kaufman Fantastic Fest 2015-0257 (27441349145) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Charlie Kaufman]], Best Original Screenplay winner]]\n[[File:Alexander Payne 8692.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Alexander Payne]], Best Adapted Screenplay co-winner]]\n[[File:Gustavo Santaolalla - 9MAR07 -presidencia-govar.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Gustavo Santaolalla]], Best Original Score winner]]\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Film|Best Film]]}}\n'''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Michael Mann]], [[Sandy Climan]], [[Graham King]] and [[Charles Evans Jr.]]'''\n* ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]'' \u2013 [[Steve Golin]] and Anthony Bregman\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Richard N. Gladstein]] and [[Nellie Bellflower]]\n* ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' \u2013 [[Michael Nozik]], Edgard Tenenbaum and Karen Tenkhoff\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Simon Channing Williams]] and [[Alain Sarde]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]]}}\n'''[[Mike Leigh]] \u2013 ''[[Vera Drake]]'''''\n* [[Marc Forster]] \u2013 ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]''\n* [[Martin Scorsese]] \u2013 ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''\n* [[Michael Mann]] \u2013 ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]''\n* [[Michel Gondry]] \u2013 ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]''\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|Best Actor in a Leading Role]]}}\n'''[[Jamie Foxx]] \u2013 ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' as [[Ray Charles]]'''\n* [[Gael Garc\u00eda Bernal]] \u2013 ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' as [[Che Guevara]]\n* [[Jim Carrey]] \u2013 ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]'' as Joel Barish\n* [[Johnny Depp]] \u2013 ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' as [[J. M. Barrie]]\n* [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] \u2013 ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' as [[Howard Hughes]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|Best Actress in a Leading Role]]}}\n'''[[Imelda Staunton]] \u2013 ''[[Vera Drake]]'' as Vera Drake'''\n* [[Charlize Theron]] \u2013 ''[[Monster (2003 film)|Monster]]'' as [[Aileen Wuornos]]\n* [[Kate Winslet]] \u2013 ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]'' as Clementine Kruczynski\n* [[Kate Winslet]] \u2013 ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' as [[Sylvia Llewelyn Davies]]\n* [[Zhang Ziyi]] \u2013 ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' as Mei\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Actor in a Supporting Role]]}}\n'''[[Clive Owen]] \u2013 ''[[Closer (2004 film)|Closer]]'' as Larry Gray'''\n* [[Alan Alda]] \u2013 ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' as [[Owen Brewster]]\n* [[Jamie Foxx]] \u2013 ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' as Max Durocher\n* [[Phil Davis (actor)|Phil Davis]] \u2013 ''[[Vera Drake]]'' as Stanley Drake\n* [[Rodrigo de la Serna]] \u2013 ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' as [[Alberto Granado]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]]}}\n'''[[Cate Blanchett]] \u2013 ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' as [[Katharine Hepburn]]'''\n* [[Heather Craney]] \u2013 ''[[Vera Drake]]'' as Joyce Drake\n* [[Julie Christie]] \u2013 ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' as Emma du Maurier\n* [[Meryl Streep]] \u2013 ''[[The Manchurian Candidate (2004 film)|The Manchurian Candidate]]'' as Eleanor Prentiss Shaw\n* [[Natalie Portman]] \u2013 ''[[Closer (2004 film)|Closer]]'' as Alice Ayres / Jane Jones\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Original Screenplay|Best Original Screenplay]]}}\n'''''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]'' \u2013 [[Charlie Kaufman]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[John Logan (writer)|John Logan]]\n* ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' \u2013 [[Stuart Beattie]]\n* ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' \u2013 [[James L. White]]\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Mike Leigh]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]}}\n'''''[[Sideways]]'' \u2013 [[Alexander Payne]] and [[Jim Taylor (writer)|Jim Taylor]]'''\n* ''[[The Chorus (2004 film)|The Chorus]]'' \u2013 [[Christophe Barratier]] and Philippe Lopes-Curval\n* ''[[Closer (2004 film)|Closer]]'' \u2013 [[Patrick Marber]]\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[David Magee]]\n* ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' \u2013 [[Jos\u00e9 Rivera (playwright)|Jos\u00e9 Rivera]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]}}\n'''''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' \u2013 [[Dion Beebe]] and [[Paul Cameron (cinematographer)|Paul Cameron]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Robert Richardson (cinematographer)|Robert Richardson]]\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Roberto Schaefer]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 [[Zhao Xiaoding]]\n* ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' \u2013 [[\u00c9ric Gautier]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]}}\n'''''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Jacqueline Durran]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]]\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Alexandra Byrne]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 [[Emi Wada]]\n* ''[[The Merchant of Venice (2004 film)|The Merchant of Venice]]'' \u2013 Sammy Sheldon\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]}}\n'''''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]'' \u2013 [[Vald\u00eds \u00d3skarsd\u00f3ttir]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Thelma Schoonmaker]]\n* ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' \u2013 [[Jim Miller (film editor)|Jim Miller]] and [[Paul Rubell]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 Long Cheng\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Jim Clark (film editor)|Jim Clark]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Makeup and Hair|Best Makeup and Hair]]}}\n'''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 Morag Ross, Kathryn Blondell and [[Si\u00e2n Grigg]]'''\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Christine Blundell]]\n* ''[[Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]'' \u2013 [[Amanda Knight]], Eithn Fennell and [[Nick Dudman]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 Kwan Lee-Na, Yang Xiaohai and Chau Siu-Mui\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Christine Blundell]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Original Music|Best Original Music]]}}\n'''''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' \u2013 [[Gustavo Santaolalla]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Howard Shore]]\n* ''[[The Chorus (2004 film)|The Chorus]]'' \u2013 [[Bruno Coulais]]\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Jan A. P. Kaczmarek]]\n* ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' \u2013 [[Craig Armstrong (composer)|Craig Armstrong]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]}}\n'''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Dante Ferretti]]'''\n* ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]'' \u2013 [[Gemma Jackson]]\n* ''[[Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]'' \u2013 [[Stuart Craig]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 Huo Tingxiao\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Eve Stewart]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Sound|Best Sound]]}}\n'''''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' \u2013 [[Steve Cantamessa]], [[Scott Millan]], [[Greg Orloff]] and [[Bob Beemer]]'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Philip Stockton]], [[Eugene Gearty]], [[Petur Hliddal]] and [[Tom Fleischman]]\n* ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' \u2013 Elliott Koretz, [[Lee Orloff]], [[Michael Minkler]] and [[Myron Nettinga]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 Tao Jing and [[Roger Savage]]\n* ''[[Spider-Man 2]]'' \u2013 [[Paul N. J. Ottosson]], [[Kevin O'Connell (sound mixer)|Kevin O'Connell]], [[Greg P. Russell]] and [[Jeffrey J. Haboush]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Special Visual Effects|Best Special Visual Effects]]}}\n'''''[[The Day After Tomorrow]]'' \u2013 [[Karen Goulekas]], [[Neil Corbould]], [[Greg and Colin Strause|Greg Strause]] and Remo Balcells'''\n* ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' \u2013 [[Robert Legato]], Pete Travers, Matthew Gratzner and Bruce Steinheimer\n* ''[[Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]'' \u2013 [[John Richardson (special effects designer)|John Richardson]], [[Roger Guyett]], [[Tim Burke (visual effects supervisor)|Tim Burke]], [[Bill George (visual effects supervisor)|Bill George]] and Karl Mooney\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 Angie Lam, Andy Brown, Kirsty Millar and Luke Hetherington\n* ''[[Spider-Man 2]]'' \u2013 [[John Dykstra]], [[Scott Stokdyk]], [[Anthony LaMolinara]] and [[John Frazier]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Outstanding British Film|Outstanding British Film]]}}\n'''''[[My Summer of Love]]'' \u2013 [[Tanya Seghatchian]], Christopher Collins and [[Pawe\u0142 Pawlikowski]]'''\n* ''[[Dead Man's Shoes (2004 film)|Dead Man's Shoes]]'' \u2013 [[Mark Herbert]] and [[Shane Meadows]]\n* ''[[Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]'' \u2013 [[David Heyman]], [[Chris Columbus (filmmaker)|Chris Columbus]], Mark Radcliffe and [[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]]\n* ''[[Shaun of the Dead]]'' \u2013 [[Nira Park]] and [[Edgar Wright]]\n* ''[[Vera Drake]]'' \u2013 [[Simon Channing Williams]], [[Alain Sarde]] and [[Mike Leigh]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Outstanding Debut by a British Writer, Director or Producer|Outstanding Debut by a British Writer, Director or Producer]]}}\n'''''[[A Way of Life]]'' \u2013 [[Amma Asante]] (Writer/Director)'''\n* ''[[AfterLife (film)|AfterLife]]'' \u2013 [[Andrea Gibb]] (Writer)\n* ''[[Dear Frankie]]'' \u2013 [[Shona Auerbach]] (Director)\n* ''[[Layer Cake (film)|Layer Cake]]'' \u2013 [[Matthew Vaughn]] (Director)\n* ''[[Shaun of the Dead]]'' \u2013 [[Nira Park]] (Producer)\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Short Animation|Best Short Animation]]}}\n'''''[[Birthday Boy (film)|Birthday Boy]]'' \u2013 Andrew Gregory and Park Se-jong'''\n* ''City Paradise'' \u2013 Erika Forzy and Gaelle Denis\n* ''Heavy Pockets'' \u2013 Jane Robertson and Sarah Cox\n* ''His Passionate Bride'' \u2013 Sylvie Bringas and Monika Forsberg\n* ''Little Things'' \u2013 Daniel Greaves\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Short Film|Best Short Film]]}}\n'''''The Banker'' \u2013 Kelly Broad and [[Hattie Dalton]]'''\n* ''Can't Stop Breathing'' \u2013 Ravinder Basra and Amy Neil\n* ''Elephant Boy'' \u2013 Rene Mohandas and Durdana Shaikh\n* ''Knitting a Love Song'' \u2013 Debbie Ballin and Annie Watson\n* ''[[Six Shooter (film)|Six Shooter]]'' \u2013 Mia Bays, [[Kenton Allen]] and [[Martin McDonagh]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\" colspan=\"2\" | {{Award category|#BDB76B|[[BAFTA Award for Best Film Not in the English Language|Best Film Not in the English Language]]}}\n'''''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]'' \u2013 [[Michael Nozik]], Edgard Tenenbaum, Karen Tenkhoff and [[Walter Salles]]'''\n* ''[[Bad Education (2004 film)|Bad Education]]'' \u2013 [[Agust\u00edn Almod\u00f3var]] and [[Pedro Almod\u00f3var]]\n* ''[[The Chorus (2004 film)|The Chorus]]'' \u2013 [[Arthur Cohn]], Nicolas Mauvernay, [[Jacques Perrin]] and [[Christophe Barratier]]\n* ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]'' \u2013 [[William Kong]] and [[Zhang Yimou]]\n* ''[[A Very Long Engagement]]'' \u2013 [[Francis Boespflug]] and [[Jean-Pierre Jeunet]]\n|}\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Films that received multiple nominations\n! style=\"background:#BDB76B;| Nominations\n! style=\"background:#BDB76B;| Film\n|-\n| 14\n| ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 11\n| ''[[Finding Neverland (film)|Finding Neverland]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Vera Drake]]''\n|-\n| 9\n| ''[[House of Flying Daggers]]''\n|-\n| 7\n| ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 6\n| ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 4\n| ''[[Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 3\n| ''[[The Chorus (2004 film)|The Chorus]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Closer (2004 film)|Closer]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2\n| ''[[Shaun of the Dead]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Spider-Man 2]]''\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Films that received multiple awards\n! style=\"background:#BDB76B;| Awards\n! style=\"background:#BDB76B;| Film\n|-\n| 4\n| ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''\n|-\n| 3\n| ''[[Vera Drake]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2\n| ''[[Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind]]''\n|-\n| ''[[The Motorcycle Diaries (film)|The Motorcycle Diaries]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[77th Academy Awards]]\n* [[30th C\u00e9sar Awards]]\n* [[10th Critics' Choice Awards]]\n* [[57th Directors Guild of America Awards]]\n* [[62nd Golden Globe Awards]]\n* [[25th Golden Raspberry Awards]]\n* [[9th Golden Satellite Awards]]\n* [[20th Independent Spirit Awards]]\n* [[10th Lumi\u00e8res Awards]]\n* [[16th Producers Guild of America Awards]]\n* [[31st Saturn Awards]]\n* [[11th Screen Actors Guild Awards]]\n* [[57th Writers Guild of America Awards]]\n\n==Sources==\n* http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,1018223,00.html Aviator leads BAFTAs with 14 nominations\n* http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-334399/Full-list-Bafta-nominees.html Full List of BAFTA nominations\n* http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4260957.stm Aviator wins Best Film\n* http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4261145.stm Stars on Red Carpet\n\n{{BAFTA Film Awards Chron}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:British Academy Film Awards, 58th}}\n[[Category:British Academy Film Awards|Film058]]\n[[Category:2004 film awards]]\n[[Category:February 2005 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{no footnotes|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number            = 58\n| award             = British Academy Film Awards\n| date              = 12 February 2005\n| site              = [[Odeon Leicester Square]], [[London]]\n| host              = [[Stephen Fry]]\n| producer          = \n| director          = \n| best_film         = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'''''\n| best_british      = '''''[[My Summer of Love]]'''''\n| best_actor        = '''[[Jamie Foxx]]'''\n| best_actor_film   = ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]''\n| best_actress      = '''[[Imelda Staunton]]'''\n| best_actress_film = ''[[Vera Drake]]''\n| most_wins         = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''''' (4)\n| most_nominations  = '''''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''''' (14)\n| channel           = \n| duration          = \n| ratings           = \n| last              = 57th\n| next              = 59th\n}}\n\nThe '''58th [[British Academy Film Awards]]''', given by the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]], took place on 12 February 2005 and honoured the best films of [[2004 in film|2004]].\n\n''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' won [[BAFTA Award for Best Film|Best Film]], Best Supporting Actress for [[Cate Blanchett]], Best Production Design, and Best Makeup and Hair. [[Jamie Foxx]] and [[Imelda Staunton]] won Best Actor and Best Actress for ''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' and ''[[Vera Drake]]'', respectively. ''Vera Drake'' also won Best Director for [[Mike Leigh]] and Best Costume Design. ''[[My Summer of Love]]'', directed by [[Pawe\u0142 Pawlikowski]], was voted Outstanding British Film of 2004.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n[[File:Mike Leigh (Berlinale 2012) cropped.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Mike Leigh]], Best Director winner]]\n[[File:Jamie Foxx by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Jamie Foxx]], Best Actor winner]]\n[[File:Imelda Staunton (2011).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Imelda Staunton]], Best Actress winner]]\n[[File:Clive Owen (Berlin Film Festival 2009).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Clive Owen]], Best Supporting Actor winner]]\n[[File:Cate Blanchett Cannes 2015.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Cate Blanchett]], Best Supporting Actress winner]]\n[[File:Charlie Kaufman Fantastic Fest 2015-0257 (27441349145) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Charlie Kaufman]], Best Original Screenplay winner]]\n[[File:Alexander Payne 8692.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Alexander Payne]], Best Adapted Screenplay co-winner]]\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! style=\"backgro